Endpoint purity and abuse scanner

Usage:
  purelink [flags]
  purelink [command]

Available Commands:
  batch       Validate endpoints from file or stdin
  check       Validate a single endpoint
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  configure   Show configuration guidance
  dedupe      Find duplicates across lists
  help        Help about any command
  import      Import endpoints
  report      Generate a full diagnostic report
  speedtest   Run an optional free download speed test
  version     Print version

Flags:
  -c, --config string   config file path
  -o, --format string   output format: table, json, csv, md (default "table")
  -h, --help            help for purelink
      --no-color        disable colored terminal output
  -t, --timeout int     timeout per check in seconds (default 10)
  -v, --verbose         enable verbose output

Use "purelink [command] --help" for more information about a command.
